The paper presents machine learning frameworks for constructing Or's of And's (OA) models, which are a type of rule-based model. This falls under the category of machine learning, specifically in the subfield of supervised learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization-based approaches, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the application of OA models as a diagnostic screening tool could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
